General.Name: Avanza Bank Holding AB
General.Description: Avanza Bank Holding AB (publ) provides online stock trading services in Sweden. The company offers share and fund, investment savings, endowment insurance, endowment child insurance, external deposit, and pension insurance savings accounts, as well as occupational pensions and individual pension plans. It also trades in equities, funds, and other securities; and provides external and green mortgages, private banking mortgages, and margin loans and lending products. In addition, the company offers decision support services; and publishes topical news and independent advice on the financial website, Placera, as well as on the weekly financial magazine, Börsveckan. It primarily serves individual investors; and professional investors and corporate customers, such as entrepreneurs and asset managers. Avanza Bank Holding AB (publ) was founded in 1999 and is headquartered in Stockholm, Sweden.
